				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hi,
<br />

<br />
After using bbAntiSpam for a week I have some suggestions for the next update which will make it an even better product.
<br />

<br />
1. Add ACP panel for configuration: this will simplify the options settings. In the ACP I would like to see:
<br />
- Option to activate or deactivate email notifications (I think on big boards getting an email every time there is a spam attempt is useless). Ability to set target email address.
<br />
- Statistics: how many spam attempts where killed. Week overview, per day with export option (?). Best is GD graphs.
<br />
- Auto update feature.
<br />
- Possibly some rules option, example would be to be excluded strings like www or callto, etc.
<br />

<br />
This is a great product and has good potential to become a standard anti spam tool for phpbb!
<br />

<br />
Cheers!
<br />

<br />
DickS</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
